headline: Visa closes US open-banking unit as data fight heats up, source says
summary: (Reuters) -Payments processor Visa has shuttered its open-banking business in the United States, according to a source familiar with the matter, as tensions mount between banks and fintechs over access to customer data.  The unit provides tools to fintechs for easier access to bank data, helping them offer smoother sign-ups and money transfers.  However, disputes between banks and fintechs have fueled doubts about the future of open banking.
